Key Trends:



Connectivity & Automation - Explosion-proof scales incorporating communication protocols like WiFi, Bluetooth to tie into broader Industrial Internet of Things (IIoT) infrastructure enabling large scale automation of materials measurement.

Composite & Non-Sparking Materials - Replacement of conventionally used metals with lightweight non-sparking composites, plastics that mitigate ignition risks and enhance portability of devices.

Analytics Integration - Inbuilt software and cloud-based analytics for tracking, monitoring weight data, identifying anomalies, and predictive maintenance across networks of hazardous area weighing instruments.

Customized Solutions - Offering custom engineered systems compatible with specific zone ratings, gas types, temperature ranges etc instead of one-size-fits all approach to ensure regulatory compliance.

Energy Efficiency - Long battery runtimes using efficient load cell designs, energy recovery and low power electronics extending maintenance cycles.

